<metal:block i18n:domain="schooltool">
  <div class="header" i18n:translate="">
    What is This?
  </div>
  <div class="body">
    <p i18n:translate="">
      In addition to entering data through SchoolTool's web interface, you
      can also import data from a spreadsheet using this template:
      <a i18n:name="link-to-empty-data-file" href="empty_data.xls"
         tal:attributes="href context/++resource++empty_data.xls">empty_data.xls</a>.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      Data included in the spreadsheet will be added to data in the system;
      importing will not cause data to be removed.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      You do not have to import all worksheets at the same time.  You can import
      individual worksheets sequentially.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      For people interested in testing and exploring SchoolTool, we provide
      a set of sample data:
      <a i18n:name="link-to-sample-data-file" href="sample_data.xls"
         tal:attributes="href context/++resource++sample_data.xls">sample_data.xls</a>.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      We also provide a large data set:
      <a i18n:name="link-to-sample-data-file" href="large_sample_data.xls"
         tal:attributes="href context/++resource++large_sample_data.xls">
        large_sample_data.xls
      </a>
      -- 1000 students over multiple years -- for performance testing.
      This set can take a very long time to be imported and may fail
      on systems with inadequate memory.
    </p>
  </div>
</metal:block>
